==Abstract==

This IIP introduces the "addrv2" message format supporting variable-length addresses for Tor v3, I2P, and CJDNS networks. It is adapted from BIP 155 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

The original "addr" message uses fixed 16-byte addresses, insufficient for:
* Tor v3 onion addresses (32 bytes)
* I2P addresses (32 bytes)
* Future network types

==Specification==

===sendaddrv2 Message===

<pre>
sendaddrv2: (empty)
</pre>

Sent during handshake to indicate addrv2 support.

===addrv2 Message===

<pre>
addrv2:
  count: varint
  addr_list: [
    {
      time:     uint32    // Unix timestamp
      services: varint    // Service flags
      networkID: uint8    // Network type
      addr:     []byte    // Variable-length address
      port:     uint16    // Port number
    },
    ...
  ]
</pre>

===Network IDs===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! ID !! Network !! Address Length
|-
| 0x01 || IPv4 || 4 bytes
|-
| 0x02 || IPv6 || 16 bytes
|-
| 0x03 || Tor v2 (deprecated) || 10 bytes
|-
| 0x04 || Tor v3 || 32 bytes
|-
| 0x05 || I2P || 32 bytes
|-
| 0x06 || CJDNS || 16 bytes
|}

===Tor v3 Address Format===

32-byte ed25519 public key. The full .onion address is derived as:
<pre>
onion = base32(pubkey || checksum || version) + ".onion"
</pre>

===I2P Address Format===

32-byte SHA-256 hash of the I2P destination. The full .b32.i2p address is:
<pre>
b32 = base32(hash) + ".b32.i2p"
</pre>

